[
    {
        "user": "U5STGTB3J",
        "type": "message",
        "ts": "1769589908.038539",
        "client_msg_id": "05C0085D-FB7D-412B-9430-ACBDB33376AE",
        "text": "There's a difference between translating one deterministic language into another, like going from assembly to C, and using stochastic patterns to translate ambiguous human language into a deterministic programming language. That doesn't mean either of those things is good or bad. It just means we're not just adding another layer, because that layer we're adding right now is not like the others.\n\n&gt; A big chunk of what we do is dumb stuff we wish we weren't.\nWacky idea: Let's redesign the dumb stuff instead of teaching a model to keep doing the dumb stuff for us.\n\nEven wackier idea: Can AI agents help us to explore the design space?\n\nA lot of artists are worried that now everybody can do their kind of art with AI and the world gets drowned in low-quality “art” while the good stuff still exists but becomes much harder to find. \nAnd yet some artists will probably use AI to elevate their art, because they learn how to apply it to their process instead of just hoping to have AI do the work for them. \nLet's be like those artists.",
        "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "source_team": "T5TCAFTA9",
        "user_profile": {
            "avatar_hash": "649181907e06",
